<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 08 at 2:34PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Rain snow and thunderstorms this afternoon...
At 230 PM, areas of rain, snow and isolated thunderstorms
continue to push northward through Southwest MT into Central MT.
Areas of snow over Southwest MT will reduce visibility below one
half mile at times, with snowfall rates up to 2 inches per hour.
Some of the stronger thunderstorms could produce pea size hail and
wind gusts near 40 mph.
Those traveling this afternoon over Central or Southwest MT should
be alert for quickly changing road conditions.</description>
